extra.description: All anecdotal information of the report, which cannot be parsed into the data harmonization elements. E.g. subject of mails, etc. This is data is not automatically propagated to the events.

feed.accuracy.description: A float between 0 and 100 that represents how accurate the data in the feed is

feed.code.description: Code name for the feed, e.g. DFGS, HSDAG etc.

feed.documentation.description: A URL or hint where to find the documentation of this feed.

feed.name.description: Name for the feed, usually found in collector bot configuration.

feed.provider.description: Name for the provider of the feed, usually found in collector bot configuration.

feed.url.description: The URL of a given abuse feed, where applicable

raw.description: The original raw and unparsed data encoded in base64.

rtir_id.description: Request Tracker Incident Response ticket id.

time.observation.description: The time the collector of the local instance processed (observed) the event.
